6872 
6882  protected virtual void DrawUnderlineMesh(Vector3 start, Vector3 end, ref int index, float startScale, float endScale, float maxScale, float sdfScale, Color32 underlineColor)
6883  {
6884  // Get Underline special character from the primary font asset.
6885  GetUnderlineSpecialCharacter(m_fontAsset);
6886 
6887  if (m_Underline.character == null)
6888  {
6889  if (!TMP_Settings.warningsDisabled)
6890  Debug.LogWarning("Unable to add underline since the primary Font Asset doesn't contain the underline character.", this);
6891 
6892  return;
6893  }
6894 
6895  int underlineMaterialIndex = m_Underline.materialIndex;
6896 
6897  int verticesCount = index + 12;
6898 
6899  // Check to make sure our current mesh buffer allocations can hold these new Quads.
6900  if (verticesCount > m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].vertices.Length)
6901  {
6902  // Resize Mesh Buffers
6903  m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].ResizeMeshInfo(verticesCount / 4);
6904  }
6905 
6906  // Adjust the position of the underline based on the lowest character. This matters for subscript character.
6907  start.y = Mathf.Min(start.y, end.y);
6908  end.y = Mathf.Min(start.y, end.y);
6909 
6910  GlyphMetrics underlineGlyphMetrics = m_Underline.character.glyph.metrics;
6911  GlyphRect underlineGlyphRect = m_Underline.character.glyph.glyphRect;
6912 
6913  float segmentWidth = underlineGlyphMetrics.width / 2 * maxScale;
6914 
6915  if (end.x - start.x < underlineGlyphMetrics.width * maxScale)
6916  {
6917  segmentWidth = (end.x - start.x) / 2f;
6918  }
6919 
6920  float startPadding = m_padding * startScale / maxScale;
6921  float endPadding = m_padding * endScale / maxScale;
6922 
6923  float underlineThickness = m_Underline.fontAsset.faceInfo.underlineThickness;
6924 
6925  // UNDERLINE VERTICES FOR (3) LINE SEGMENTS
6926  #region UNDERLINE VERTICES
6927  Vector3[] vertices = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].vertices;
6928 
6929  // Front Part of the Underline
6930  vertices[index + 0] = start + new Vector3(0, 0 - (underlineThickness + m_padding) * maxScale, 0); // BL
6931  vertices[index + 1] = start + new Vector3(0, m_padding * maxScale, 0); // TL
6932  vertices[index + 2] = vertices[index + 1] + new Vector3(segmentWidth, 0, 0); // TR
6933  vertices[index + 3] = vertices[index + 0] + new Vector3(segmentWidth, 0, 0); // BR
6934 
6935  // Middle Part of the Underline
6936  vertices[index + 4] = vertices[index + 3]; // BL
6937  vertices[index + 5] = vertices[index + 2]; // TL
6938  vertices[index + 6] = end + new Vector3(-segmentWidth, m_padding * maxScale, 0); // TR
6939  vertices[index + 7] = end + new Vector3(-segmentWidth, -(underlineThickness + m_padding) * maxScale, 0); // BR
6940 
6941  // End Part of the Underline
6942  vertices[index + 8] = vertices[index + 7]; // BL
6943  vertices[index + 9] = vertices[index + 6]; // TL
6944  vertices[index + 10] = end + new Vector3(0, m_padding * maxScale, 0); // TR
6945  vertices[index + 11] = end + new Vector3(0, -(underlineThickness + m_padding) * maxScale, 0); // BR
6946  #endregion
6947 
6948  // UNDERLINE UV0
6949  #region HANDLE UV0
6950  Vector2[] uvs0 = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].uvs0;
6951 
6952  int atlasWidth = m_Underline.fontAsset.atlasWidth;
6953  int atlasHeight = m_Underline.fontAsset.atlasHeight;
6954 
6955  // Calculate UV required to setup the 3 Quads for the Underline.
6956  Vector2 uv0 = new Vector2((underlineGlyphRect.x - startPadding) / atlasWidth, (underlineGlyphRect.y - m_padding) / atlasHeight); // bottom left
6957  Vector2 uv1 = new Vector2(uv0.x, (underlineGlyphRect.y + underlineGlyphRect.height + m_padding) / atlasHeight); // top left
6958  Vector2 uv2 = new Vector2((underlineGlyphRect.x - startPadding + (float)underlineGlyphRect.width / 2) / atlasWidth, uv1.y); // Mid Top Left
6959  Vector2 uv3 = new Vector2(uv2.x, uv0.y); // Mid Bottom Left
6960  Vector2 uv4 = new Vector2((underlineGlyphRect.x + endPadding + (float)underlineGlyphRect.width / 2) / atlasWidth, uv1.y); // Mid Top Right
6961  Vector2 uv5 = new Vector2(uv4.x, uv0.y); // Mid Bottom right
6962  Vector2 uv6 = new Vector2((underlineGlyphRect.x + endPadding + underlineGlyphRect.width) / atlasWidth, uv1.y); // End Part - Bottom Right
6963  Vector2 uv7 = new Vector2(uv6.x, uv0.y); // End Part - Top Right
6964 
6965  // Left Part of the Underline
6966  uvs0[0 + index] = uv0; // BL
6967  uvs0[1 + index] = uv1; // TL
6968  uvs0[2 + index] = uv2; // TR
6969  uvs0[3 + index] = uv3; // BR
6970 
6971  // Middle Part of the Underline
6972  uvs0[4 + index] = new Vector2(uv2.x - uv2.x * 0.001f, uv0.y);
6973  uvs0[5 + index] = new Vector2(uv2.x - uv2.x * 0.001f, uv1.y);
6974  uvs0[6 + index] = new Vector2(uv2.x + uv2.x * 0.001f, uv1.y);
6975  uvs0[7 + index] = new Vector2(uv2.x + uv2.x * 0.001f, uv0.y);
6976 
6977  // Right Part of the Underline
6978  uvs0[8 + index] = uv5;
6979  uvs0[9 + index] = uv4;
6980  uvs0[10 + index] = uv6;
6981  uvs0[11 + index] = uv7;
6982  #endregion
6983 
6984  // UNDERLINE UV2
6985  #region HANDLE UV2 - SDF SCALE
6986  // UV1 contains Face / Border UV layout.
6987  float min_UvX = 0;
6988  float max_UvX = (vertices[index + 2].x - start.x) / (end.x - start.x);
6989 
6990  //Calculate the xScale or how much the UV's are getting stretched on the X axis for the middle section of the underline.
6991  float xScale = Mathf.Abs(sdfScale);
6992 
6993  Vector2[] uvs2 = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].uvs2;
6994 
6995  uvs2[0 + index] = PackUV(0, 0, xScale);
6996  uvs2[1 + index] = PackUV(0, 1, xScale);
6997  uvs2[2 + index] = PackUV(max_UvX, 1, xScale);
6998  uvs2[3 + index] = PackUV(max_UvX, 0, xScale);
6999 
7000  min_UvX = (vertices[index + 4].x - start.x) / (end.x - start.x);
7001  max_UvX = (vertices[index + 6].x - start.x) / (end.x - start.x);
7002 
7003  uvs2[4 + index] = PackUV(min_UvX, 0, xScale);
7004  uvs2[5 + index] = PackUV(min_UvX, 1, xScale);
7005  uvs2[6 + index] = PackUV(max_UvX, 1, xScale);
7006  uvs2[7 + index] = PackUV(max_UvX, 0, xScale);
7007 
7008  min_UvX = (vertices[index + 8].x - start.x) / (end.x - start.x);
7009 
7010  uvs2[8 + index] = PackUV(min_UvX, 0, xScale);
7011  uvs2[9 + index] = PackUV(min_UvX, 1, xScale);
7012  uvs2[10 + index] = PackUV(1, 1, xScale);
7013  uvs2[11 + index] = PackUV(1, 0, xScale);
7014  #endregion
7015 
7016  // UNDERLINE VERTEX COLORS
7017  #region UNDERLINE VERTEX COLORS
7018  // Alpha is the lower of the vertex color or tag color alpha used.
7019  underlineColor.a = m_fontColor32.a < underlineColor.a ? m_fontColor32.a : underlineColor.a;
7020 
7021  Color32[] colors32 = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].colors32;
7022  colors32[0 + index] = underlineColor;
7023  colors32[1 + index] = underlineColor;
7024  colors32[2 + index] = underlineColor;
7025  colors32[3 + index] = underlineColor;
7026 
7027  colors32[4 + index] = underlineColor;
7028  colors32[5 + index] = underlineColor;
7029  colors32[6 + index] = underlineColor;
7030  colors32[7 + index] = underlineColor;
7031 
7032  colors32[8 + index] = underlineColor;
7033  colors32[9 + index] = underlineColor;
7034  colors32[10 + index] = underlineColor;
7035  colors32[11 + index] = underlineColor;
7036  #endregion
7037 
7038  index += 12;
7039  }
7040

7042  protected virtual void DrawTextHighlight(Vector3 start, Vector3 end, ref int index, Color32 highlightColor)
7043  {
7044  if (m_Underline.character == null)
7045  {
7046  GetUnderlineSpecialCharacter(m_fontAsset);
7047 
7048  if (m_Underline.character == null)
7049  {
7050  if (!TMP_Settings.warningsDisabled)
7051  Debug.LogWarning("Unable to add highlight since the primary Font Asset doesn't contain the underline character.", this);
7052 
7053  return;
7054  }
7055  }
7056 
7057  int underlineMaterialIndex = m_Underline.materialIndex;
7058 
7059  int verticesCount = index + 4;
7060 
7061  // Check to make sure our current mesh buffer allocations can hold these new Quads.
7062  if (verticesCount > m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].vertices.Length)
7063  {
7064  // Resize Mesh Buffers
7065  m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].ResizeMeshInfo(verticesCount / 4);
7066  }
7067 
7068  // UNDERLINE VERTICES FOR (3) LINE SEGMENTS
7069  #region HIGHLIGHT VERTICES
7070  Vector3[] vertices = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].vertices;
7071 
7072  // Front Part of the Underline
7073  vertices[index + 0] = start; // BL
7074  vertices[index + 1] = new Vector3(start.x, end.y, 0); // TL
7075  vertices[index + 2] = end; // TR
7076  vertices[index + 3] = new Vector3(end.x, start.y, 0); // BR
7077  #endregion
7078 
7079  // UNDERLINE UV0
7080  #region HANDLE UV0
7081  Vector2[] uvs0 = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].uvs0;
7082 
7083  int atlasWidth = m_Underline.fontAsset.atlasWidth;
7084  int atlasHeight = m_Underline.fontAsset.atlasHeight;
7085  GlyphRect glyphRect = m_Underline.character.glyph.glyphRect;
7086 
7087  // Calculate UV
7088  Vector2 uv0 = new Vector2(((float)glyphRect.x + glyphRect.width / 2) / atlasWidth, (glyphRect.y + (float)glyphRect.height / 2) / atlasHeight); // bottom left
7089 
7090  // UVs for the Quad
7091  uvs0[0 + index] = uv0; // BL
7092  uvs0[1 + index] = uv0; // TL
7093  uvs0[2 + index] = uv0; // TR
7094  uvs0[3 + index] = uv0; // BR
7095  #endregion
7096 
7097  // HIGHLIGHT UV2
7098  #region HANDLE UV2 - SDF SCALE
7099  Vector2[] uvs2 = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].uvs2;
7100  Vector2 customUV = new Vector2(0, 1);
7101  uvs2[0 + index] = customUV;
7102  uvs2[1 + index] = customUV;
7103  uvs2[2 + index] = customUV;
7104  uvs2[3 + index] = customUV;
7105  #endregion
7106 
7107  // HIGHLIGHT VERTEX COLORS
7108  #region
7109  // Alpha is the lower of the vertex color or tag color alpha used.
7110  highlightColor.a = m_fontColor32.a < highlightColor.a ? m_fontColor32.a : highlightColor.a;
7111 
7112  Color32[] colors32 = m_textInfo.meshInfo[underlineMaterialIndex].colors32;
7113  colors32[0 + index] = highlightColor;
7114  colors32[1 + index] = highlightColor;
7115  colors32[2 + index] = highlightColor;
7116  colors32[3 + index] = highlightColor;
7117  #endregion
7118 
7119  index += 4;
7120  }

7126  protected void LoadDefaultSettings()
7127  {
7128  if (m_fontAsset == null || m_isWaitingOnResourceLoad)
7129  {
7130  m_rectTransform = this.rectTransform;
7131 
7132  if (TMP_Settings.autoSizeTextContainer)
7133  {
7134  autoSizeTextContainer = true;
7135  }
7136  else
7137  {
7138  if (GetType() == typeof(TextMeshPro))
7139  {
7140  if (m_rectTransform.sizeDelta == new Vector2(100, 100))
7141  m_rectTransform.sizeDelta = TMP_Settings.defaultTextMeshProTextContainerSize;
7142  }
7143  else
7144  {
7145  if (m_rectTransform.sizeDelta == new Vector2(100, 100))
7146  m_rectTransform.sizeDelta = TMP_Settings.defaultTextMeshProUITextContainerSize;
7147  }
7148 
7149  }
7150 
7151  m_enableWordWrapping = TMP_Settings.enableWordWrapping;
7152  m_enableKerning = TMP_Settings.enableKerning;
7153  m_enableExtraPadding = TMP_Settings.enableExtraPadding;
7154  m_tintAllSprites = TMP_Settings.enableTintAllSprites;
7155  m_parseCtrlCharacters = TMP_Settings.enableParseEscapeCharacters;
7156  m_fontSize = m_fontSizeBase = TMP_Settings.defaultFontSize;
7157  m_fontSizeMin = m_fontSize * TMP_Settings.defaultTextAutoSizingMinRatio;
7158  m_fontSizeMax = m_fontSize * TMP_Settings.defaultTextAutoSizingMaxRatio;
7159  m_isWaitingOnResourceLoad = false;
7160  raycastTarget = TMP_Settings.enableRaycastTarget;
7161  m_IsTextObjectScaleStatic = TMP_Settings.isTextObjectScaleStatic;
7162  }
7163  else if ((int)m_textAlignment < 0xFF)
7164  {
7165  // Convert Legacy TextAlignmentOptions enumerations from Unity 5.2 / 5.3.
7166  m_textAlignment = TMP_Compatibility.ConvertTextAlignmentEnumValues(m_textAlignment);
7167  }
7168 
7169  // Convert text alignment to independent horizontal and vertical alignment properties
7170  if (m_textAlignment != TextAlignmentOptions.Converted)
7171  {
7172  m_HorizontalAlignment = (HorizontalAlignmentOptions)((int)m_textAlignment & 0xFF);
7173  m_VerticalAlignment = (VerticalAlignmentOptions)((int)m_textAlignment & 0xFF00);
7174  m_textAlignment = TextAlignmentOptions.Converted;
7175  }
7176  }

7191  protected void GetEllipsisSpecialCharacter(TMP_FontAsset fontAsset)
7192  {
7193  bool isUsingAlternativeTypeface;
7194 
7195  // Search base font asset
7196  TMP_Character character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAsset(0x2026, fontAsset, false, m_FontStyleInternal, m_FontWeightInternal, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7197 
7198  if (character == null)
7199  {
7200  // Search primary fallback list
7201  if (fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable != null && fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable.Count > 0)
7202  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAssets(0x2026, fontAsset, fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable, true, m_FontStyleInternal, m_FontWeightInternal, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7203  }
7204 
7205  // Search TMP Settings general fallback list
7206  if (character == null)
7207  {
7208  if (TMP_Settings.fallbackFontAssets != null && TMP_Settings.fallbackFontAssets.Count > 0)
7209  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAssets(0x2026, fontAsset, TMP_Settings.fallbackFontAssets, true, m_FontStyleInternal, m_FontWeightInternal, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7210  }
7211 
7212  // Search TMP Settings' default font asset
7213  if (character == null)
7214  {
7215  if (TMP_Settings.defaultFontAsset != null)
7216  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAsset(0x2026, TMP_Settings.defaultFontAsset, true, m_FontStyleInternal, m_FontWeightInternal, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7217  }
7218 
7219  if (character != null)
7220  m_Ellipsis = new SpecialCharacter(character, 0);
7221  }

7302  protected TMP_FontAsset GetFontAssetForWeight(int fontWeight)
7303  {
7304  bool isItalic = (m_FontStyleInternal & FontStyles.Italic) == FontStyles.Italic || (m_fontStyle & FontStyles.Italic) == FontStyles.Italic;
7305 
7306  TMP_FontAsset fontAsset = null;
7307 
7308  int weightIndex = fontWeight / 100;
7309 
7310  if (isItalic)
7311  fontAsset = m_currentFontAsset.fontWeightTable[weightIndex].italicTypeface;
7312  else
7313  fontAsset = m_currentFontAsset.fontWeightTable[weightIndex].regularTypeface;

7318  internal TMP_TextElement GetTextElement(uint unicode, TMP_FontAsset fontAsset, FontStyles fontStyle, FontWeight fontWeight, out bool isUsingAlternativeTypeface)
7319  {
7320  TMP_Character character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAsset(unicode, fontAsset, false, fontStyle, fontWeight, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7321 
7322  if (character != null)
7323  return character;
7324 
7325  // Search potential list of fallback font assets assigned to the font asset.
7326  if (fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable != null && fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable.Count > 0)
7327  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAssets(unicode, fontAsset, fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable, true, fontStyle, fontWeight, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7328 
7329  if (character != null)
7330  {
7331  // Add character to font asset lookup cache
7332  //fontAsset.AddCharacterToLookupCache(unicode, character);
7333 
7334  return character;
7335  }
7336 
7337  // Search for the character in the primary font asset if not the current font asset
7338  if (fontAsset.instanceID != m_fontAsset.instanceID)
7339  {
7340  // Search primary font asset
7341  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAsset(unicode, m_fontAsset, false, fontStyle, fontWeight, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7342 
7343  // Use material and index of primary font asset.
7344  if (character != null)
7345  {
7346  m_currentMaterialIndex = 0;
7347  m_currentMaterial = m_materialReferences[0].material;
7348 
7349  // Add character to font asset lookup cache
7350  //fontAsset.AddCharacterToLookupCache(unicode, character);
7351 
7352  return character;
7353  }
7354 
7355  // Search list of potential fallback font assets assigned to the primary font asset.
7356  if (m_fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable != null && m_fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable.Count > 0)
7357  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAssets(unicode, fontAsset, m_fontAsset.m_FallbackFontAssetTable, true, fontStyle, fontWeight, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7358 
7359  if (character != null)
7360  {
7361  // Add character to font asset lookup cache
7362  //fontAsset.AddCharacterToLookupCache(unicode, character);
7363 
7364  return character;
7365  }
7366  }
7367 
7368  // Search for the character in potential local Sprite Asset assigned to the text object.
7369  if (m_spriteAsset != null)
7370  {
7371  TMP_SpriteCharacter spriteCharacter = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetSpriteCharacterFromSpriteAsset(unicode, m_spriteAsset, true);
7372 
7373  if (spriteCharacter != null)
7374  return spriteCharacter;
7375  }
7376 
7377  // Search for the character in the list of fallback assigned in the TMP Settings (General Fallbacks).
7378  if (TMP_Settings.fallbackFontAssets != null && TMP_Settings.fallbackFontAssets.Count > 0)
7379  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAssets(unicode, fontAsset, TMP_Settings.fallbackFontAssets, true, fontStyle, fontWeight, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7380 
7381  if (character != null)
7382  {
7383  // Add character to font asset lookup cache
7384  //fontAsset.AddCharacterToLookupCache(unicode, character);
7385 
7386  return character;
7387  }
7388 
7389  // Search for the character in the Default Font Asset assigned in the TMP Settings file.
7390  if (TMP_Settings.defaultFontAsset != null)
7391  character = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetCharacterFromFontAsset(unicode, TMP_Settings.defaultFontAsset, true, fontStyle, fontWeight, out isUsingAlternativeTypeface);
7392 
7393  if (character != null)
7394  {
7395  // Add character to font asset lookup cache
7396  //fontAsset.AddCharacterToLookupCache(unicode, character);
7397 
7398  return character;
7399  }
7400 
7401  // Search for the character in the Default Sprite Asset assigned in the TMP Settings file.
7402  if (TMP_Settings.defaultSpriteAsset != null)
7403  {
7404  TMP_SpriteCharacter spriteCharacter = TMP_FontAssetUtilities.GetSpriteCharacterFromSpriteAsset(unicode, TMP_Settings.defaultSpriteAsset, true);
7405 
7406  if (spriteCharacter != null)
7407  return spriteCharacter;
7408  }
7409 
7410  return null;
7411  }

7443  public virtual string GetParsedText()
7444  {
7445  if (m_textInfo == null)
7446  return string.Empty;
7447 
7448  int characterCount = m_textInfo.characterCount;
7449 
7450  // TODO - Could implement some static buffer pool shared by all instances of TMP objects.
7451  char[] buffer = new char[characterCount];
7452 
7453  for (int i = 0; i < characterCount && i < m_textInfo.characterInfo.Length; i++)
7454  {
7455  buffer[i] = m_textInfo.characterInfo[i].character;
7456  }
7457 
7458  return new string(buffer);
7459  }

7462  internal bool IsSelfOrLinkedAncestor(TMP_Text targetTextComponent)
7463  {
7464  if (targetTextComponent == null)
7465  return true;
7466 
7467  if (parentLinkedComponent != null)
7468  {
7469  if (parentLinkedComponent.IsSelfOrLinkedAncestor(targetTextComponent))
7470  return true;
7471  }
7472 
7473  if (this.GetInstanceID() == targetTextComponent.GetInstanceID())
7474  return true;
7475 
7476  return false;
7477  }
7478 
7479  internal void ReleaseLinkedTextComponent(TMP_Text targetTextComponent)
7480  {
7481  if (targetTextComponent == null)
7482  return;
7483 
7484  TMP_Text childLinkedComponent = targetTextComponent.linkedTextComponent;
7485 
7486  if (childLinkedComponent != null)
7487  ReleaseLinkedTextComponent(childLinkedComponent);
7488 
7489  targetTextComponent.text = string.Empty;
7490  targetTextComponent.firstVisibleCharacter = 0;
7491  targetTextComponent.linkedTextComponent = null;
7492  targetTextComponent.parentLinkedComponent = null;
7493  }

7523  protected Vector2 PackUV(float x, float y, float scale)
7524  {
7525  Vector2 output;
7526 
7527  output.x = (int)(x * 511);
7528  output.y = (int)(y * 511);
7529 
7530  output.x = (output.x * 4096) + output.y;
7531  output.y = scale;
7532 
7533  return output;
7534  }

7596  protected int HexToInt(char hex)
7597  {
7598  switch (hex)
7599  {
7600  case '0': return 0;
7601  case '1': return 1;
7602  case '2': return 2;
7603  case '3': return 3;
7604  case '4': return 4;
7605  case '5': return 5;
7606  case '6': return 6;
7607  case '7': return 7;
7608  case '8': return 8;
7609  case '9': return 9;
7610  case 'A': return 10;
7611  case 'B': return 11;
7612  case 'C': return 12;
7613  case 'D': return 13;
7614  case 'E': return 14;
7615  case 'F': return 15;
7616  case 'a': return 10;
7617  case 'b': return 11;
7618  case 'c': return 12;
7619  case 'd': return 13;
7620  case 'e': return 14;
7621  case 'f': return 15;
7622  }
7623  return 15;
7624  }

7727  protected Color32 HexCharsToColor(char[] hexChars, int tagCount)
7728  {
7729  if (tagCount == 4)
7730  {
7731  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[1]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[1]));
7732  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[2]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[2]));
7733  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[3]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[3]));
7734 
7735  return new Color32(r, g, b, 255);
7736  }
7737  else if (tagCount == 5)
7738  {
7739  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[1]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[1]));
7740  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[2]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[2]));
7741  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[3]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[3]));
7742  byte a = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[4]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[4]));
7743 
7744  return new Color32(r, g, b, a);
7745  }
7746  else if (tagCount == 7)
7747  {
7748  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[1]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[2]));
7749  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[3]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[4]));
7750  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[5]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[6]));
7751 
7752  return new Color32(r, g, b, 255);
7753  }
7754  else if (tagCount == 9)
7755  {
7756  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[1]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[2]));
7757  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[3]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[4]));
7758  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[5]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[6]));
7759  byte a = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[7]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[8]));
7760 
7761  return new Color32(r, g, b, a);
7762  }
7763  else if (tagCount == 10)
7764  {
7765  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[7]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[7]));
7766  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[8]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[8]));
7767  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[9]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[9]));
7768 
7769  return new Color32(r, g, b, 255);
7770  }
7771  else if (tagCount == 11)
7772  {
7773  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[7]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[7]));
7774  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[8]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[8]));
7775  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[9]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[9]));
7776  byte a = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[10]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[10]));
7777 
7778  return new Color32(r, g, b, a);
7779  }
7780  else if (tagCount == 13)
7781  {
7782  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[7]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[8]));
7783  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[9]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[10]));
7784  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[11]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[12]));
7785 
7786  return new Color32(r, g, b, 255);
7787  }
7788  else if (tagCount == 15)
7789  {
7790  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[7]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[8]));
7791  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[9]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[10]));
7792  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[11]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[12]));
7793  byte a = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[13]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[14]));
7794 
7795  return new Color32(r, g, b, a);
7796  }
7797 
7798  return new Color32(255, 255, 255, 255);
7799  }
7800 
7801 
7809  protected Color32 HexCharsToColor(char[] hexChars, int startIndex, int length)
7810  {
7811  if (length == 7)
7812  {
7813  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 1]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 2]));
7814  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 3]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 4]));
7815  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 5]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 6]));
7816 
7817  return new Color32(r, g, b, 255);
7818  }
7819  else if (length == 9)
7820  {
7821  byte r = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 1]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 2]));
7822  byte g = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 3]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 4]));
7823  byte b = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 5]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 6]));
7824  byte a = (byte)(HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 7]) * 16 + HexToInt(hexChars[startIndex + 8]));
7825 
7826  return new Color32(r, g, b, a);
7827  }
7828 
7829  return s_colorWhite;
7830  }
7831 
7832 
7841  int GetAttributeParameters(char[] chars, int startIndex, int length, ref float[] parameters)
7842  {
7843  int endIndex = startIndex;
7844  int attributeCount = 0;
7845 
7846  while (endIndex < startIndex + length)
7847  {
7848  parameters[attributeCount] = ConvertToFloat(chars, startIndex, length, out endIndex);
7849 
7850  length -= (endIndex - startIndex) + 1;
7851  startIndex = endIndex + 1;
7852 
7853  attributeCount += 1;
7854  }
7855 
7856  return attributeCount;
7857  }
7858 
7859 
7867  protected float ConvertToFloat(char[] chars, int startIndex, int length)
7868  {
7869  int lastIndex;
7870 
7871  return ConvertToFloat(chars, startIndex, length, out lastIndex);
7872  }
7873 
7874 
7883  protected float ConvertToFloat(char[] chars, int startIndex, int length, out int lastIndex)
7884  {
7885  if (startIndex == 0)
7886  {
7887  lastIndex = 0;
7888  return Int16.MinValue;
7889  }
7890 
7891  int endIndex = startIndex + length;
7892 
7893  bool isIntegerValue = true;
7894  float decimalPointMultiplier = 0;
7895 
7896  // Set value multiplier checking the first character to determine if we are using '+' or '-'
7897  int valueSignMultiplier = 1;
7898  if (chars[startIndex] == '+')
7899  {
7900  valueSignMultiplier = 1;
7901  startIndex += 1;
7902  }
7903  else if (chars[startIndex] == '-')
7904  {
7905  valueSignMultiplier = -1;
7906  startIndex += 1;
7907  }
7908 
7909  float value = 0;
7910 
7911  for (int i = startIndex; i < endIndex; i++)
7912  {
7913  uint c = chars[i];
7914 
7915  if (c >= '0' && c <= '9' || c == '.')
7916  {
7917  if (c == '.')
7918  {
7919  isIntegerValue = false;
7920  decimalPointMultiplier = 0.1f;
7921  continue;
7922  }
7923 
7924  //Calculate integer and floating point value
7925  if (isIntegerValue)
7926  value = value * 10 + (c - 48) * valueSignMultiplier;
7927  else
7928  {
7929  value = value + (c - 48) * decimalPointMultiplier * valueSignMultiplier;
7930  decimalPointMultiplier *= 0.1f;
7931  }
7932 
7933  continue;
7934  }
7935  else if (c == ',')
7936  {
7937  if (i + 1 < endIndex && chars[i + 1] == ' ')
7938  lastIndex = i + 1;
7939  else
7940  lastIndex = i;
7941 
7942  // Make sure value is within reasonable range.
7943  if (value > 32767)
7944  return Int16.MinValue;
7945 
7946  return value;
7947  }
7948  }
7949 
7950  lastIndex = endIndex;
7951 
7952  // Make sure value is within reasonable range.
7953  if (value > 32767)
7954  return Int16.MinValue;
7955 
7956  return value;
7957  }
7958 
7959 
7967  protected bool ValidateHtmlTag(UnicodeChar[] chars, int startIndex, out int endIndex)
7968  {
7969  int tagCharCount = 0;
7970  byte attributeFlag = 0;
7971 
7972  int attributeIndex = 0;
7973  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode = 0;
7974  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode = 0;
7975  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = 0;
7976  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength = 0;
7977  TagValueType tagValueType = m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.None;
7978  TagUnitType tagUnitType = m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
7979 
7980  // Clear attribute name hash codes
7981  m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode = 0;
7982  m_xmlAttribute[2].nameHashCode = 0;
7983  m_xmlAttribute[3].nameHashCode = 0;
7984  m_xmlAttribute[4].nameHashCode = 0;
7985 
7986  endIndex = startIndex;
7987  bool isTagSet = false;
7988  bool isValidHtmlTag = false;
7989 
7990  for (int i = startIndex; i < chars.Length && chars[i].unicode != 0 && tagCharCount < m_htmlTag.Length && chars[i].unicode != '<'; i++)
7991  {
7992  int unicode = chars[i].unicode;
7993 
7994  if (unicode == '>') // ASCII Code of End HTML tag '>'
7995  {
7996  isValidHtmlTag = true;
7997  endIndex = i;
7998  m_htmlTag[tagCharCount] = (char)0;
7999  break;
8000  }
8001 
8002  m_htmlTag[tagCharCount] = (char)unicode;
8003  tagCharCount += 1;
8004 
8005  if (attributeFlag == 1)
8006  {
8007  if (tagValueType == TagValueType.None)
8008  {
8009  // Check for attribute type
8010  if (unicode == '+' || unicode == '-' || unicode == '.' || (unicode >= '0' && unicode <= '9'))
8011  {
8012  tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8013  tagValueType = m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.NumericalValue;
8014  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = tagCharCount - 1;
8015  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength += 1;
8016  }
8017  else if (unicode == '#')
8018  {
8019  tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8020  tagValueType = m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.ColorValue;
8021  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = tagCharCount - 1;
8022  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength += 1;
8023  }
8024  else if (unicode == '"')
8025  {
8026  tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8027  tagValueType = m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.StringValue;
8028  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = tagCharCount;
8029  }
8030  else
8031  {
8032  tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8033  tagValueType = m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.StringValue;
8034  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = tagCharCount - 1;
8035  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode = (m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode << 5) + m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode ^ unicode;
8036  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength += 1;
8037  }
8038  }
8039  else
8040  {
8041  if (tagValueType == TagValueType.NumericalValue)
8042  {
8043  // Check for termination of numerical value.
8044  if (unicode == 'p' || unicode == 'e' || unicode == '%' || unicode == ' ')
8045  {
8046  attributeFlag = 2;
8047  tagValueType = TagValueType.None;
8048 
8049  switch (unicode)
8050  {
8051  case 'e':
8052  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = tagUnitType = TagUnitType.FontUnits;
8053  break;
8054  case '%':
8055  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Percentage;
8056  break;
8057  default:
8058  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8059  break;
8060  }
8061 
8062  attributeIndex += 1;
8063  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode = 0;
8064  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode = 0;
8065  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.None;
8066  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8067  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = 0;
8068  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength = 0;
8069 
8070  }
8071  else if (attributeFlag != 2)
8072  {
8073  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength += 1;
8074  }
8075  }
8076  else if (tagValueType == TagValueType.ColorValue)
8077  {
8078  if (unicode != ' ')
8079  {
8080  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength += 1;
8081  }
8082  else
8083  {
8084  attributeFlag = 2;
8085  tagValueType = TagValueType.None;
8086  tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8087  attributeIndex += 1;
8088  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode = 0;
8089  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.None;
8090  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8091  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode = 0;
8092  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = 0;
8093  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength = 0;
8094  }
8095  }
8096  else if (tagValueType == TagValueType.StringValue)
8097  {
8098  // Compute HashCode value for the named tag.
8099  if (unicode != '"')
8100  {
8101  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode = (m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode << 5) + m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode ^ unicode;
8102  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength += 1;
8103  }
8104  else
8105  {
8106  attributeFlag = 2;
8107  tagValueType = TagValueType.None;
8108  tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8109  attributeIndex += 1;
8110  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode = 0;
8111  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.None;
8112  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8113  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode = 0;
8114  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = 0;
8115  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength = 0;
8116  }
8117  }
8118  }
8119  }
8120 
8121 
8122  if (unicode == '=') // '='
8123  attributeFlag = 1;
8124 
8125  // Compute HashCode for the name of the attribute
8126  if (attributeFlag == 0 && unicode == ' ')
8127  {
8128  if (isTagSet) return false;
8129 
8130  isTagSet = true;
8131  attributeFlag = 2;
8132 
8133  tagValueType = TagValueType.None;
8134  tagUnitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8135  attributeIndex += 1;
8136  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode = 0;
8137  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueType = TagValueType.None;
8138  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].unitType = TagUnitType.Pixels;
8139  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueHashCode = 0;
8140  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueStartIndex = 0;
8141  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].valueLength = 0;
8142  }
8143 
8144  if (attributeFlag == 0)
8145  m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode = (m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode << 3) - m_xmlAttribute[attributeIndex].nameHashCode + unicode;
8146 
8147  if (attributeFlag == 2 && unicode == ' ')
8148  attributeFlag = 0;
8149 
8150  }
8151 
8152  if (!isValidHtmlTag)
8153  {
8154  return false;
8155  }
8156 
8157  //Debug.Log("Tag is [" + m_htmlTag.ArrayToString() + "]. Tag HashCode: " + m_xmlAttribute[0].nameHashCode + " Tag Value HashCode: " + m_xmlAttribute[0].valueHashCode + " Attribute 1 HashCode: " + m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode + " Value HashCode: " + m_xmlAttribute[1].valueHashCode);
8158  //for (int i = 0; i < attributeIndex; i++)
8159  // Debug.Log("Tag [" + i + "] with HashCode: " + m_xmlAttribute[i].nameHashCode + " has value of [" + new string(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueLength) + "] Numerical Value: " + ConvertToFloat(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueLength));
8160 
8161  #region Rich Text Tag Processing
8162  #if !RICH_TEXT_ENABLED
8163  // Special handling of the no parsing tag </noparse> </NOPARSE> tag
8164  if (tag_NoParsing && (m_xmlAttribute[0].nameHashCode != 53822163 && m_xmlAttribute[0].nameHashCode != 49429939))
8165  return false;
8166  else if (m_xmlAttribute[0].nameHashCode == 53822163 || m_xmlAttribute[0].nameHashCode == 49429939)
8167  {
8168  tag_NoParsing = false;
8169  return true;
8170  }
8171 
8172  // Color <#FFF> 3 Hex values (short form)
8173  if (m_htmlTag[0] == 35 && tagCharCount == 4)
8174  {
8175  m_htmlColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, tagCharCount);
8176  m_colorStack.Add(m_htmlColor);
8177  return true;
8178  }
8179  // Color <#FFF7> 4 Hex values with alpha (short form)
8180  else if (m_htmlTag[0] == 35 && tagCharCount == 5)
8181  {
8182  m_htmlColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, tagCharCount);
8183  m_colorStack.Add(m_htmlColor);
8184  return true;
8185  }
8186  // Color <#FF00FF>
8187  else if (m_htmlTag[0] == 35 && tagCharCount == 7) // if Tag begins with # and contains 7 characters.
8188  {
8189  m_htmlColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, tagCharCount);
8190  m_colorStack.Add(m_htmlColor);
8191  return true;
8192  }
8193  // Color <#FF00FF00> with alpha
8194  else if (m_htmlTag[0] == 35 && tagCharCount == 9) // if Tag begins with # and contains 9 characters.
8195  {
8196  m_htmlColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, tagCharCount);
8197  m_colorStack.Add(m_htmlColor);
8198  return true;
8199  }
8200  else
8201  {
8202  float value = 0;
8203 
8204  switch (m_xmlAttribute[0].nameHashCode)
8205  {
8206  case 98: // <b>
8207  case 66: // <B>
8208  m_FontStyleInternal |= FontStyles.Bold;
8209  m_fontStyleStack.Add(FontStyles.Bold);
8210 
8211  m_FontWeightInternal = FontWeight.Bold;
8212  return true;
8213  case 427: // </b>
8214  case 395: // </B>
8215  if ((m_fontStyle & FontStyles.Bold) != FontStyles.Bold)
8216  {
8217  if (m_fontStyleStack.Remove(FontStyles.Bold) == 0)
8218  {
8219  m_FontStyleInternal &= ~FontStyles.Bold;
8220  m_FontWeightInternal = m_FontWeightStack.Peek();
8221  }
8222  }
8223  return true;
8224  case 105: // <i>
8225  case 73: // <I>
8226  m_FontStyleInternal |= FontStyles.Italic;
8227  m_fontStyleStack.Add(FontStyles.Italic);
8228 
8229  if (m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode == 276531 || m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode == 186899)
8230  {
8231  m_ItalicAngle = (int)ConvertToFloat(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[1].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[1].valueLength);
8232 
8233  // Make sure angle is within valid range.
8234  if (m_ItalicAngle < -180 || m_ItalicAngle > 180) return false;
8235  }
8236  else
8237  m_ItalicAngle = m_currentFontAsset.italicStyle;
8238 
8239  m_ItalicAngleStack.Add(m_ItalicAngle);
8240 
8241  return true;
8242  case 434: // </i>
8243  case 402: // </I>
8244  if ((m_fontStyle & FontStyles.Italic) != FontStyles.Italic)
8245  {
8246  m_ItalicAngle = m_ItalicAngleStack.Remove();
8247 
8248  if (m_fontStyleStack.Remove(FontStyles.Italic) == 0)
8249  m_FontStyleInternal &= ~FontStyles.Italic;
8250  }
8251  return true;
8252  case 115: // <s>
8253  case 83: // <S>
8254  m_FontStyleInternal |= FontStyles.Strikethrough;
8255  m_fontStyleStack.Add(FontStyles.Strikethrough);
8256 
8257  if (m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode == 281955 || m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode == 192323)
8258  {
8259  m_strikethroughColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[1].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[1].valueLength);
8260  m_strikethroughColor.a = m_htmlColor.a < m_strikethroughColor.a ? (byte)(m_htmlColor.a) : (byte)(m_strikethroughColor .a);
8261  }
8262  else
8263  m_strikethroughColor = m_htmlColor;
8264 
8265  m_strikethroughColorStack.Add(m_strikethroughColor);
8266 
8267  return true;
8268  case 444: // </s>
8269  case 412: // </S>
8270  if ((m_fontStyle & FontStyles.Strikethrough) != FontStyles.Strikethrough)
8271  {
8272  if (m_fontStyleStack.Remove(FontStyles.Strikethrough) == 0)
8273  m_FontStyleInternal &= ~FontStyles.Strikethrough;
8274  }
8275 
8276  m_strikethroughColor = m_strikethroughColorStack.Remove();
8277  return true;
8278  case 117: // <u>
8279  case 85: // <U>
8280  m_FontStyleInternal |= FontStyles.Underline;
8281  m_fontStyleStack.Add(FontStyles.Underline);
8282 
8283  if (m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode == 281955 || m_xmlAttribute[1].nameHashCode == 192323)
8284  {
8285  m_underlineColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[1].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[1].valueLength);
8286  m_underlineColor.a = m_htmlColor.a < m_underlineColor.a ? (byte)(m_htmlColor.a) : (byte)(m_underlineColor.a);
8287  }
8288  else
8289  m_underlineColor = m_htmlColor;
8290 
8291  m_underlineColorStack.Add(m_underlineColor);
8292 
8293  return true;
8294  case 446: // </u>
8295  case 414: // </U>
8296  if ((m_fontStyle & FontStyles.Underline) != FontStyles.Underline)
8297  {
8298  m_underlineColor = m_underlineColorStack.Remove();
8299 
8300  if (m_fontStyleStack.Remove(FontStyles.Underline) == 0)
8301  m_FontStyleInternal &= ~FontStyles.Underline;
8302  }
8303 
8304  m_underlineColor = m_underlineColorStack.Remove();
8305  return true;
8306  case 43045: // <mark=#FF00FF80>
8307  case 30245: // <MARK>
8308  m_FontStyleInternal |= FontStyles.Highlight;
8309  m_fontStyleStack.Add(FontStyles.Highlight);
8310 
8311  Color32 highlightColor = new Color32(255, 255, 0, 64);
8312  TMP_Offset highlightPadding = TMP_Offset.zero;
8313 
8314  // Handle Mark Tag and potential attributes
8315  for (int i = 0; i < m_xmlAttribute.Length && m_xmlAttribute[i].nameHashCode != 0; i++)
8316  {
8317  int nameHashCode = m_xmlAttribute[i].nameHashCode;
8318 
8319  switch (nameHashCode)
8320  {
8321  // Mark tag
8322  case 43045:
8323  case 30245:
8324  if (m_xmlAttribute[i].valueType == TagValueType.ColorValue)
8325  highlightColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[0].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[0].valueLength);
8326  break;
8327 
8328  // Color attribute
8329  case 281955:
8330  highlightColor = HexCharsToColor(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueLength);
8331  break;
8332 
8333  // Padding attribute
8334  case 15087385:
8335  int paramCount = GetAttributeParameters(m_htmlTag, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueStartIndex, m_xmlAttribute[i].valueLength, ref m_attributeParameterValues);
8336  if (paramCount != 4) return false;
8337 
8338  highlightPadding = new TMP_Offset(m_attributeParameterValues[0], m_attributeParameterValues[1], m_attributeParameterValues[2], m_attributeParameterValues[3]);
8339  highlightPadding *= m_fontSize * 0.01f * (m_isOrthographic ? 1 : 0.1f);
8340  break;
8341  }
8342  }
8343 
8344  highlightColor.a = m_htmlColor.a < highlightColor.a ? (byte)(m_htmlColor.a) : (byte)(highlightColor.a);
8345 
8346  HighlightState state = new HighlightState(highlightColor, highlightPadding);
8347  m_HighlightStateStack.Push(state);
8348 
8349  return true;
8350  case 155892: // </mark>
8351  case 143092: // </MARK>
8352  if ((m_fontStyle & FontStyles.Highlight) != FontStyles.Highlight)
8353  {
8354  m_HighlightStateStack.Remove();
8355 
8356  if (m_fontStyleStack.Remove(FontStyles.Highlight) == 0)
8357  m_FontStyleInternal &= ~FontStyles.Highlight;
8358  }
8359  return true;
8360  case 6552: // <sub>
8361  case 4728: // <SUB>
8362  m_fontScaleMultiplier *= m_currentFontAsset.faceInfo.subscriptSize > 0 ? m_currentFontAsset.faceInfo.subscriptSize : 1;
8363  m_baselineOffsetStack.Push(m_baselineOffset);
8364  m_baselineOffset += m_currentFontAsset.faceInfo.subscriptOffset * m_fontScale * m_fontScaleMultiplier;
8365 
8366  m_fontStyleStack.Add(FontStyles.Subscript);
8367  m_FontStyleInternal |= FontStyles.Subscript;
8368  return true;
8369  case 22673: // </sub>
8370  case 20849: // </SUB>
8371  if ((m_FontStyleInternal & FontStyles.Subscript) == FontStyles.Subscript)
8372  {
8373  if (m_fontScaleMultiplier < 1)
8374  {
8375  //m_baselineOffset -= m_currentFontAsset.fontInfo.SubscriptOffset * m_fontScale * m_fontScaleMultiplier;
8376  m_baselineOffset = m_baselineOffsetStack.Pop();
8377  m_fontScaleMultiplier /= m_currentFontAsset.faceInfo.subscriptSize > 0 ? m_currentFontAsset.faceInfo.subscriptSize : 1;
